1
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:20,000
JONAH HEX (2010)

2
00:01:11,415 --> 00:01:14,907
<i>War and me took to each other real well.</i>

3
00:01:28,665 --> 00:01:30,155
<i>It felt like it had meaning.</i>

4
00:01:36,540 --> 00:01:38,974
<i>The feeling of doing
what you thought was right.</i>

5
00:01:44,147 --> 00:01:46,012
<i>But it wasn't.</i>

6
00:01:51,688 --> 00:01:53,315
<i>Folks can believe what they like...</i>

7
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:57,859
<i>...but eventually a man's gotta decide
if he's gonna do what's right.</i>

8
00:02:20,283 --> 00:02:23,719
<i>That choice cost me
more than I bargained for.</i>

9
00:02:31,528 --> 00:02:33,291
Daddy!

10
00:02:37,434 --> 00:02:39,527
Daddy!

11
00:02:39,936 --> 00:02:41,733
- Daddy!
- Son!

12
00:02:42,506 --> 00:02:44,565
Brave boy.

13
00:02:44,741 --> 00:02:47,733
My son Jeb was brave. Loyal too.

14
00:02:47,911 --> 00:02:51,176
And then he was murdered
by his best friend in cold blood.

15
00:02:51,348 --> 00:02:52,713
Isn't that right, Hex?

16
00:02:52,883 --> 00:02:54,180
Turnbull, let them go.

17
00:02:55,018 --> 00:02:58,078
Son, you are not fit to wear this uniform.

18
00:02:58,255 --> 00:03:00,120
You're a coward and a traitor.

19
00:03:00,524 --> 00:03:03,584
Fine. I am.

20
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,284
It's got nothing to do with them.

21
00:03:05,462 --> 00:03:06,929
- Of course it does.
No.

22
00:03:07,097 --> 00:03:08,860
You killed the only family I had.

23
00:03:09,032 --> 00:03:11,000
No. General, please, don't do this.

24
00:03:11,168 --> 00:03:14,569
Betrayed your own men
and you murdered my son.

25
00:03:14,738 --> 00:03:17,002
I'm begging you, sir. I'm begging you.

26
00:03:17,174 --> 00:03:21,235
You took everything that I love,
Jonah Hex.

27
00:03:21,411 --> 00:03:22,878
You know what that feels like?

28
00:03:23,046 --> 00:03:24,604
Don't do this.

29
00:03:24,781 --> 00:03:26,874
It feels like this.

30
00:03:27,884 --> 00:03:29,112
I want you to watch.

31
00:03:29,286 --> 00:03:30,753
No! No!

32
00:03:30,921 --> 00:03:33,412
- No!
No!

33
00:03:57,748 --> 00:03:59,716
You're gonna go free.

34
00:03:59,883 --> 00:04:02,852
Free to walk this earth
with a mark on your flesh.

35
00:04:03,019 --> 00:04:06,284
And every day,
that mark will remind you...

36
00:04:06,456 --> 00:04:10,517
...of the man
who took everything you had.

37
00:04:20,937 --> 00:04:23,963
<i>I hung on that cross for days.</i>

38
00:04:26,076 --> 00:04:30,308
<i>By the time the Crow Indians found me
and cut me down...</i>

39
00:04:31,515 --> 00:04:33,210
<i>...I was nearly dead.</i>

40
00:04:33,383 --> 00:04:36,819
<i>Those medicine men did
what they could to bring me back...</i>

41
00:04:36,987 --> 00:04:39,615
<i>...but somehow they just couldn't
get me all the way out.</i>

42
00:04:39,790 --> 00:04:42,884
<i>And crows seemed to stay with me.</i>

43
00:04:43,994 --> 00:04:45,427
<i>Didn't make me immortal.</i>

44
00:04:45,595 --> 00:04:49,463
<i>Just left me with the curse
of knowing the other side.</i>

45
00:04:52,602 --> 00:04:55,935
<i>See, talking to dead folks ain't natural.</i>

46
00:04:56,106 --> 00:04:58,870
<i>But sometimes they're the only ones
who will point the way.</i>

47
00:05:02,112 --> 00:05:07,243
<i>I searched this land high and low,
hunting old Turnbull down.</i>

48
00:05:08,018 --> 00:05:14,423
<i>But then that old bastard played one
final trick on me and died in a hotel fire.</i>

49
00:05:15,525 --> 00:05:18,983
<i>The man that took my family was dead.</i>

50
00:05:20,363 --> 00:05:23,855
<i>I had nowhere to go
and a heart full of vengeance.</i>

51
00:05:24,034 --> 00:05:27,800
<i>I did what come natural
and turned to bounty hunting.</i>

52
00:05:30,574 --> 00:05:32,735
<i>Punishing the guilty
wherever there was profit.</i>

53
00:05:40,483 --> 00:05:42,951
<i>This here's my story.</i>

54
00:06:41,344 --> 00:06:43,904
Jonah Hex.

55
00:06:47,951 --> 00:06:50,078
Jonah Hex.

56
00:06:53,823 --> 00:06:55,723
These are the boys you wanted.

57
00:06:55,892 --> 00:06:58,258
The Clayton boys.

58
00:06:58,428 --> 00:06:59,588
That's right.

59
00:06:59,763 --> 00:07:01,924
Appear we have a little problem, Mr. Hex.

60
00:07:02,098 --> 00:07:05,261
There's four Clayton boys.
This only three boys.

61
00:07:05,769 --> 00:07:08,499
I don't see my way we could
possibly recompense you...

62
00:07:08,672 --> 00:07:10,833
...the agreed upon "recomseption. "

63
00:07:17,814 --> 00:07:19,714
The rest of him was too fat for my horse.

64
00:07:19,883 --> 00:07:21,680
Well, now, Mr. Hex...

65
00:07:21,851 --> 00:07:26,311
...these boys were no end of trouble
to us simple folk.

66
00:07:27,524 --> 00:07:31,460
You showed me proof they was
guilty. I brought them in, simple as that.

67
00:07:31,628 --> 00:07:34,529
You surely have done us quite a favor.

68
00:07:34,931 --> 00:07:37,627
Transaction's all it was.

69
00:07:38,001 --> 00:07:40,868
I'll collect my $100 bounty on them
and be on my way.

70
00:07:41,037 --> 00:07:45,531
That there, Mr. Hex,
was more of a limited-time offer.

71
00:07:45,709 --> 00:07:47,472
But you'll pay it all the same.

72
00:07:47,644 --> 00:07:50,511
Oh, hell, Mr. Hex.

73
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:57,313
There's an unscrupulous man or two would
pay double that for your stinking hide.

74
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:02,687
Five coffins.

75
00:08:06,563 --> 00:08:07,996
Sure you don't need eight?

76
00:08:08,164 --> 00:08:09,324
Cut him down!

77
00:09:45,128 --> 00:09:46,288
Congratulations.

78
00:10:46,022 --> 00:10:47,922
Hang it up.
All right. I'm in.

79
00:11:41,377 --> 00:11:42,435
Mom?

80
00:11:43,012 --> 00:11:45,503
What do you suppose
those men are doing?

81
00:11:49,519 --> 00:11:51,316
Get down!

82
00:12:05,335 --> 00:12:08,566
Stay calm.
We've got them 20 to one.

83
00:12:23,753 --> 00:12:25,186
Prepare to engage!

84
00:12:37,934 --> 00:12:39,401
Look out!

85
00:12:44,607 --> 00:12:46,837
I'll take out the conductor!

86
00:12:47,010 --> 00:12:48,136
Secure the weapon!

87
00:12:52,315 --> 00:12:53,612
Nobody move.

88
00:12:54,050 --> 00:12:55,574
Everybody, get back.

89
00:13:19,075 --> 00:13:20,702
We're slowing down.

90
00:13:43,666 --> 00:13:47,693
You're sure, absolutely sure,
it was Turnbull?

91
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:49,337
Positive, President Grant.

92
00:13:49,505 --> 00:13:51,871
Bastard must've faked his own death.

93
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:54,066
- Why now?
I can hazard a guess.

94
00:13:54,577 --> 00:13:58,274
There are centennial celebrations
being prepared in more than 20 states.

95
00:13:58,815 --> 00:14:00,942
Whatever he's preparing...

96
00:14:02,585 --> 00:14:04,746
<i>...we've probably got 10 days
to find him.</i>

97
00:14:04,921 --> 00:14:05,910
<i>Beg your pardon...</i>

98
00:14:06,089 --> 00:14:09,217
<i>...but why does the president care
if one old Confederate general is alive?</i>

99
00:14:09,392 --> 00:14:12,327
<i>After Gettysburg, Turnbull changed.</i>

100
00:14:12,495 --> 00:14:15,293
<i>He targeted hospitals, schools, churches.</i>

101
00:14:15,765 --> 00:14:17,733
<i>Strike enough fear into people's hearts...</i>

102
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:21,927
<i>...and eventually they'll tear down
the government that failed to protect them.</i>

103
00:14:22,105 --> 00:14:24,938
<i>His Mexican slaves
had a nickname for him.</i>

104
00:14:25,341 --> 00:14:26,808
<i>- What was it?
- Terorrista.</i>

105
00:14:26,976 --> 00:14:28,967
<i>Terorrista.</i>

106
00:14:33,883 --> 00:14:36,249
Load all that cannon onto our wagon.

107
00:14:36,652 --> 00:14:40,645
Find what's left of our two boys
and give them an honorable burial.

108
00:14:40,823 --> 00:14:42,085
Burn the rest.

109
00:14:43,526 --> 00:14:45,118
<i>Tell me what you know, lieutenant.</i>

110
00:14:45,294 --> 00:14:48,422
All we can confirm is that Turnbull
took something off that train.

111
00:14:48,831 --> 00:14:53,029
And that he broke into the U.S. Armory
in Virginia a week before that.

112
00:14:53,936 --> 00:14:55,733
- Summerland, Virginia?
- Yes, sir.

113
00:14:56,372 --> 00:14:57,464
He's building it.

114
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:00,609
- The plans were never completed.
- He's building the weapon.

115
00:15:00,777 --> 00:15:04,269
Sir, as you know,
my unit is the very best.

116
00:15:04,447 --> 00:15:10,215
Yes, lieutenant, which is why
I need you to locate this man.

117
00:15:12,955 --> 00:15:14,479
<i>Jonah Hex?
Mm.</i>

118
00:15:14,657 --> 00:15:17,387
<i>Hex is a lawless bounty hunter.
The man was a hero once.</i>

119
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:22,827
<i>Sir, we've all heard the stories, but...
Hex turned in Turnbull and his men.</i>

120
00:15:22,999 --> 00:15:24,967
<i>And he paid a terrible price for it.</i>

121
00:15:25,134 --> 00:15:28,160
- Sir, Turn...
- Mark my words, gentlemen.

122
00:15:28,337 --> 00:15:33,468
The very fate of our nation may rest
on the shoulders of Jonah Hex.

123
00:15:45,521 --> 00:15:47,682
He don't look so tough.

124
00:15:49,725 --> 00:15:51,818
Looks tough to me.

125
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,491
Not to me.

126
00:15:59,902 --> 00:16:01,631
Watch this.

127
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:06,304
Hey, Hex. What happened to your face?

128
00:16:12,915 --> 00:16:15,349
Cut myself shaving.

129
00:16:15,518 --> 00:16:17,509
What happened to yours?

130
00:16:21,924 --> 00:16:24,256
For the broken window.

131
00:16:41,611 --> 00:16:43,943
It's about time for you to move on,
Mr. Nash.

132
00:16:44,113 --> 00:16:46,308
Grayden, please.

133
00:16:46,482 --> 00:16:48,382
Door's right there.

134
00:16:48,985 --> 00:16:51,647
Will you at least consider it?

135
00:16:51,821 --> 00:16:54,790
I'll leave her, the store.

136
00:16:54,957 --> 00:16:56,891
Hell, my kids.

137
00:16:57,727 --> 00:16:58,751
Let's go to the city.

138
00:16:58,995 --> 00:17:02,123
I don't play house.
Our transaction is done here.

139
00:17:02,298 --> 00:17:04,528
You wanna see me,
pay fair like everyone else.

140
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:06,998
I don't want anybody else's hands
on you, Lilah.

141
00:17:10,439 --> 00:17:13,272
- Mr. Nash.
- All right.

142
00:17:13,442 --> 00:17:16,206
All right. I'll see you tomorrow.

143
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:32,791
Look, buzzard...

144
00:17:36,265 --> 00:17:37,562
Jonah Hex.

145
00:17:38,367 --> 00:17:39,959
Lilah.

146
00:17:41,938 --> 00:17:43,303
Get inside.

147
00:17:54,450 --> 00:17:56,850
It's been a while, Hex.

148
00:17:57,887 --> 00:18:00,219
Yeah, that it has.

149
00:18:06,729 --> 00:18:09,289
You worry about me, don't you?

150
00:18:14,103 --> 00:18:15,866
No.

151
00:18:21,243 --> 00:18:25,179
Well, I worry about you.

152
00:18:26,048 --> 00:18:28,812
Look how many times you've been shot.

153
00:18:29,585 --> 00:18:31,348
It's just one more that's gonna do it.

154
00:18:32,855 --> 00:18:37,053
Well, it seems like I've been
luckier than most in that respect.

155
00:18:43,933 --> 00:18:45,332
Which one was the first one?

156
00:18:45,735 --> 00:18:47,828
I don't recall a first or last.

157
00:18:51,874 --> 00:18:57,107
Why don't we call this one number one?

158
00:18:58,347 --> 00:19:00,042
This can be number two.

159
00:19:05,054 --> 00:19:06,078
Three.

160
00:19:11,260 --> 00:19:13,023
Four.

161
00:19:29,111 --> 00:19:31,511
It ain't safe here, Jonah.

162
00:19:32,181 --> 00:19:33,614
They'll be coming for you.

163
00:19:33,783 --> 00:19:36,251
Yeah, well, they always do.

164
00:19:36,652 --> 00:19:38,916
I saw them notices.

165
00:19:39,088 --> 00:19:40,715
It's different this time.

166
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:42,955
You killed them lawmen.

167
00:19:43,125 --> 00:19:46,219
They was wearing badges,
but not one of them was no lawman.

168
00:19:46,395 --> 00:19:48,329
You'll hang for it...

169
00:19:48,497 --> 00:19:51,330
...if the Army don't gun you down first.

170
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:56,331
Well...

171
00:19:57,239 --> 00:19:59,434
...then I'll be moving on.

172
00:20:00,676 --> 00:20:02,906
Maybe southways.

173
00:20:03,879 --> 00:20:05,676
Of course you are.

174
00:20:07,883 --> 00:20:09,316
It's paradise, you know...

175
00:20:10,186 --> 00:20:12,313
...waiting around here on you.

176
00:20:15,691 --> 00:20:18,091
We can go somewhere.

177
00:20:18,894 --> 00:20:22,125
Everyone who gets close to me dies.

178
00:20:23,232 --> 00:20:25,666
There's no future for you and me, Lilah.

179
00:20:26,502 --> 00:20:29,164
Look at you, setting the rules.

180
00:20:39,448 --> 00:20:42,747
You know, you shouldn't be
so sure of me, Jonah Hex.

181
00:20:43,686 --> 00:20:46,519
Next time you come around
I may not be here.

182
00:20:46,856 --> 00:20:49,654
It's the best I can do, Lilah.

183
00:20:51,427 --> 00:20:53,588
Christ, woman,
how many men you seeing a day?

184
00:20:53,763 --> 00:20:55,560
Jonah Hex?

185
00:20:55,731 --> 00:20:59,895
By Presidential Act you are hereby
inducted into military service.

186
00:21:00,069 --> 00:21:03,596
A reward will be offered
for the administration of your duties.

187
00:21:04,039 --> 00:21:05,939
Your country needs you.

188
00:21:06,642 --> 00:21:08,667
Ain't my country.

189
00:21:08,844 --> 00:21:11,335
You get lost or get dead.

190
00:21:11,514 --> 00:21:13,982
- Hex, you've got to come with us.
- No.

191
00:21:14,150 --> 00:21:16,744
You can't outshoot a dozen men.

192
00:21:18,087 --> 00:21:19,645
I might like them odds.

193
00:21:20,022 --> 00:21:21,717
Quentin Turnbull...

194
00:21:22,525 --> 00:21:24,652
You dare say that name to me?

195
00:21:28,164 --> 00:21:29,529
Quentin Turnbull is alive.

196
00:21:52,221 --> 00:21:53,745
<i>Turnbull.</i>

197
00:21:53,923 --> 00:21:55,447
<i>He's alive.</i>

198
00:21:55,624 --> 00:21:58,024
<i>I thought I'd never hear that name again.</i>

199
00:22:06,001 --> 00:22:07,901
Thank you so much for joining us,
Mr. Hex.

200
00:22:09,905 --> 00:22:12,237
The boy told me to talk to you.
Where's Turnbull?

201
00:22:12,408 --> 00:22:15,809
The president seems to think
that you're special.

202
00:22:15,978 --> 00:22:18,538
Magic, even. We'll just see about that.

203
00:22:18,714 --> 00:22:21,512
- You don't know, do you?
- Oh, we know.

204
00:22:22,785 --> 00:22:26,346
Frankly, what I don't know
is why we're even bothering with you.

205
00:22:28,090 --> 00:22:29,421
Let me show you something.

206
00:22:32,161 --> 00:22:35,153
This is the future, Hex.

207
00:22:35,331 --> 00:22:37,959
Intelligence. Information.

208
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:41,534
With our sophisticated network,
men like you will be a thing of the past.

209
00:22:43,172 --> 00:22:44,469
When we get this strung up...

210
00:22:48,377 --> 00:22:49,742
Future's bright.

211
00:22:49,912 --> 00:22:52,005
Now, you listen to me, bounty hunter.

212
00:22:52,181 --> 00:22:55,617
I have quality intelligence that says
Turnbull and his band of bastards...

213
00:22:55,784 --> 00:22:57,547
...are headed to Springfield, Georgia.

214
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:00,814
And how'd you come by this quality...

215
00:23:00,990 --> 00:23:02,719
What'd you call it?

216
00:23:02,892 --> 00:23:05,588
- Intelligence.
- Right.

217
00:23:07,229 --> 00:23:09,720
Turnbull's men assaulted
one of our trains.

218
00:23:09,899 --> 00:23:13,665
Yet we did manage to overcome
this one deadly outlaw.

219
00:23:13,936 --> 00:23:16,097
Told us everything we needed to know.

220
00:23:16,272 --> 00:23:19,105
Unfortunately he died
during our interrogation.

221
00:23:20,276 --> 00:23:22,540
I wanna talk to him.

222
00:23:23,145 --> 00:23:24,703
He's dead, Hex.

223
00:23:24,880 --> 00:23:27,906
Yeah, I'll have a word with him
all the same.

224
00:23:41,897 --> 00:23:43,865
How you doing there?

225
00:23:44,333 --> 00:23:46,995
- What's happening to me?
- Afraid you're dead, friend.

226
00:23:47,169 --> 00:23:48,534
How can you speak to me?

227
00:23:48,704 --> 00:23:51,832
Well, it's kind of a knack I picked up
when I near died myself.

228
00:23:57,513 --> 00:23:58,844
I can make it stop.

229
00:23:59,982 --> 00:24:01,950
Just need to get some information first.

230
00:24:02,117 --> 00:24:05,177
You see, what I done to you is unnatural.

231
00:24:05,354 --> 00:24:09,484
I keep you out of the ground too long,
you're likely to just burn right on up.

232
00:24:09,959 --> 00:24:13,861
And it seems like the fresher dead you are,
the quicker it happens.

233
00:24:14,196 --> 00:24:17,029
Being dead, you can see
the comings and goings...

234
00:24:17,199 --> 00:24:19,394
...of anyone you knew
when you was alive.

235
00:24:19,568 --> 00:24:20,660
What do you want?

236
00:24:21,770 --> 00:24:23,533
I'm looking for Quentin Turnbull.

237
00:24:24,073 --> 00:24:25,506
Never knew Turnbull.

238
00:24:25,674 --> 00:24:28,472
- Who recruited you?
- Make the pain stop.

239
00:24:28,644 --> 00:24:31,010
- Who?
- Make the pain stop.

240
00:24:32,581 --> 00:24:34,173
Who?

241
00:24:37,252 --> 00:24:38,719
- Slocum.
- What?

242
00:24:38,887 --> 00:24:41,355
<i>Royal Slocum.</i>

243
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:46,721
- Where?
- Runs a fight tent.

244
00:24:46,895 --> 00:24:48,226
Down in South Carolina.

245
00:25:02,845 --> 00:25:04,870
Dirt likes dead, dead likes dirt.

246
00:25:05,047 --> 00:25:06,912
Simple as that.

247
00:25:10,319 --> 00:25:11,843
Hey, wait.

248
00:25:12,021 --> 00:25:13,989
What is that sound?

249
00:25:14,156 --> 00:25:16,317
Oh, them?

250
00:25:16,492 --> 00:25:19,518
Them's likely hellhounds.

251
00:25:20,696 --> 00:25:22,823
Reckon they smell fresh meat.

