00:51:04,338 --> 00:51:07,466
We've increased military
presence, but due to his willingness...

503
00:51:07,641 --> 00:51:12,010
...to strike civilian targets, it is impossible
to predict where he's going to attack.

504
00:51:25,459 --> 00:51:28,019
I don't know
how we're gonna stop him, sir.

505
00:51:29,229 --> 00:51:30,753
Lovely.

506
00:51:33,901 --> 00:51:35,892
<i>If I stepped in
Then she stepped out again</i>

507
00:51:36,070 --> 00:51:37,662
<i>Learning to dance for Lanigan's ball</i>

508
00:51:37,838 --> 00:51:41,365
<i>Six long years I spent in Dublin
Six long years doin' nothin' at all</i>

509
00:51:41,542 --> 00:51:45,342
<i>Six long years I spent in Dublin
Learning to dance for Lanigan's ball</i>

510
00:51:51,986 --> 00:51:53,715
Hello there, little lamb.

511
00:51:59,159 --> 00:52:00,387
Have you lost your flock?

512
00:52:00,961 --> 00:52:03,191
I'm done working for the night.

513
00:52:11,338 --> 00:52:14,330
- What the hell's wrong with you?
- Just for a little fun, like.

514
00:52:18,045 --> 00:52:19,239
Nobody has to get hurt.

515
00:52:30,658 --> 00:52:32,888
Little flower, huh?

516
00:52:35,396 --> 00:52:36,624
Come on.

517
00:52:36,797 --> 00:52:38,355
Come on.

518
00:52:40,501 --> 00:52:42,799
You're coming with me, girl.

519
00:54:06,172 --> 00:54:07,537
<i>This one's about a war hero.</i>

520
00:54:09,141 --> 00:54:11,109
This one's about a war hero,
like you were.

521
00:54:11,277 --> 00:54:13,871
This man ain't near
as handsome as me.

522
00:54:14,046 --> 00:54:16,173
And where's the brave little son, Travis?

523
00:54:16,849 --> 00:54:20,341
As literary form, these things is useless.

524
00:54:20,520 --> 00:54:24,889
Now, I can feel your brain rotting
right below my hand right as we speak.

525
00:54:34,800 --> 00:54:35,960
Help! Jonah!

526
00:54:37,703 --> 00:54:40,604
You took everything I love, Jonah Hex.

527
00:54:40,773 --> 00:54:42,707
Do you know what that feels like?

528
00:54:47,079 --> 00:54:48,910
It feels like this.

529
00:54:51,050 --> 00:54:52,074
I want you to watch.

530
00:54:52,251 --> 00:54:54,048
Help! Jonah!

531
00:54:54,220 --> 00:54:57,815
No! No! No!

532
00:55:19,478 --> 00:55:20,502
Turnbull!

533
00:55:26,485 --> 00:55:29,147
Send a message to Grass, lieutenant,
U.S. Army.

534
00:55:30,523 --> 00:55:32,855
<i>Located Turnbull. Stop.</i>

535
00:55:33,025 --> 00:55:35,152
<i>Sailing out of Independence Harbor. Stop.</i>

536
00:55:35,328 --> 00:55:37,592
<i>Destination unknown. Stop.</i>

537
00:55:37,763 --> 00:55:40,698
Turnbull has constructed
nation-killer weapon. Stop.

538
00:55:45,471 --> 00:55:46,768
Going in alone.

539
00:55:46,939 --> 00:55:50,272
Send everything you got
or thousands will die. Stop.

540
00:56:44,563 --> 00:56:45,860
Whoa.

541
00:56:51,070 --> 00:56:54,733
Keep him fed and watered.
Don't you tie him up.

542
00:56:54,907 --> 00:56:57,205
If I don't come back for a spell,
he'll know it.

543
00:56:57,376 --> 00:56:58,843
He'll head out on his own way.

544
00:56:59,412 --> 00:57:01,175
He got a name?

545
00:57:01,714 --> 00:57:03,443
Yeah.

546
00:57:03,949 --> 00:57:05,780
Horse.

547
00:57:06,652 --> 00:57:07,676
You.

548
00:57:10,923 --> 00:57:12,823
Yeah, I...

549
00:57:15,695 --> 00:57:17,856
I don't know what to say to you.

550
00:57:36,515 --> 00:57:38,483
The hell you think you're going, mister?

551
00:57:41,087 --> 00:57:42,884
What happened to your fa...?

552
00:57:45,257 --> 00:57:48,715
I'm about all out
of wiseass answers, friend.

553
00:58:05,077 --> 00:58:10,014
Well, Mr. Turnbull, it appears the bells
are finally ready to toll on Washington.

554
00:58:10,182 --> 00:58:14,642
And I hear them, Mr. Lusk,
as I've heard them for six long years.

555
00:58:15,187 --> 00:58:19,453
We appreciate the services
that you have rendered to us.

556
00:58:20,259 --> 00:58:21,920
I can only hope you succeed.

557
00:58:22,094 --> 00:58:24,187
I'll most certainly hang if you don't...

558
00:58:24,363 --> 00:58:27,594
...an outcome I sincerely hope to avoid.

559
00:58:31,904 --> 00:58:34,031
Consider it avoided.

560
00:58:34,206 --> 00:58:35,673
- Fire it up.
- Let's go!

561
00:58:36,142 --> 00:58:37,734
Fire up the engine!

562
00:58:37,910 --> 00:58:40,378
Get ready to put her in the water!

563
00:58:46,852 --> 00:58:50,151
Looks good. Come on, let's go.
Check the engine room.

564
01:00:22,548 --> 01:00:25,073
You know you look like a right freak,
don't you?

565
01:00:25,251 --> 01:00:29,813
Tell me, what's it like to go through life
with a face like that?

566
01:00:32,057 --> 01:00:33,217
Let me show you.

567
01:00:48,073 --> 01:00:49,870
This is for...

568
01:00:51,944 --> 01:00:53,502
...my wife.

569
01:01:14,033 --> 01:01:16,331
This is for my son!

570
01:01:25,544 --> 01:01:28,240
Turnbull! Turnbull! Turnbull!

571
01:01:28,547 --> 01:01:31,607
Turnbull! Turnbull! Turnbull!

572
01:01:35,487 --> 01:01:37,478
Gentlemen...

573
01:01:38,324 --> 01:01:40,485
...tonight we put this ship in the water.

574
01:01:40,659 --> 01:01:41,683
Yeah!

575
01:01:42,094 --> 01:01:46,690
And as we navigate the shoreline
of this precious and ruined land...

576
01:01:46,865 --> 01:01:49,891
...let us not forget that we sail...

577
01:01:50,069 --> 01:01:51,866
...on an ocean of tears.

578
01:01:52,037 --> 01:01:53,504
And when we reach the Potomac...

579
01:01:53,672 --> 01:01:57,665
...our enemy will learn that
we have arrived to do that thing...

580
01:01:57,843 --> 01:02:02,371
...which we most assuredly
were convened to do.

581
01:02:02,548 --> 01:02:05,142
- Yeah!
- To make war!

582
01:02:05,317 --> 01:02:06,682
Yeah!

583
01:02:07,753 --> 01:02:10,244
- The Capitol will burn!
- Yeah!

584
01:02:11,490 --> 01:02:13,321
The battle is joined!

585
01:02:27,106 --> 01:02:30,234
Turnbull! Turnbull! Turnbull!

586
01:02:31,443 --> 01:02:33,035
Hex.

587
01:02:37,516 --> 01:02:39,575
You know, Hex,
they say you have no heart.

588
01:02:39,752 --> 01:02:43,051
I think your problem may be
just the contrary, son.

589
01:02:43,889 --> 01:02:44,913
You are soft.

590
01:02:45,391 --> 01:02:47,689
You're incapable of sacrifice.

591
01:02:48,394 --> 01:02:51,192
You wanna surrender or
you wanna watch another one die?

592
01:02:57,903 --> 01:02:58,927
That's a good boy.

593
01:03:03,709 --> 01:03:05,734
Once a coward, always a coward.

594
01:03:07,413 --> 01:03:09,074
Jeb says hi.

595
01:03:09,248 --> 01:03:11,273
No. I want him to watch.

596
01:03:29,034 --> 01:03:30,865
Three minutes till we're in range, sir.

597
01:03:44,716 --> 01:03:46,183
Our country was new...

598
01:03:54,660 --> 01:03:56,150
Four thousand yards to target.

599
01:04:01,400 --> 01:04:04,335
- You still got that Derringer
in your bustle? - No, he took it.

600
01:04:04,503 --> 01:04:06,767
- What about that knife in your garter?
- Took it.

601
01:04:07,139 --> 01:04:09,403
- What about that...?
- Took it all, Jonah.

602
01:04:09,575 --> 01:04:12,510
Well, searched you pretty darn good,
didn't they?

603
01:04:12,678 --> 01:04:14,976
- Wouldn't you?
- Yeah.

604
01:04:15,147 --> 01:04:17,047
All right, here's what we're gonna do.

605
01:04:17,216 --> 01:04:19,514
You shout for the guard,
get him over here...

606
01:04:19,685 --> 01:04:22,518
...and use your feminine wiles
and whatnot.

607
01:04:22,688 --> 01:04:24,781
When he gets close...

608
01:04:25,824 --> 01:04:29,521
- What the hell?
- Tallula Black's mama didn't raise no fool.

609
01:04:29,695 --> 01:04:32,721
- Tallula?
- Lilah's a nickname.

610
01:04:34,366 --> 01:04:35,526
Tallula.

611
01:04:36,702 --> 01:04:37,726
Tallula.

612
01:04:37,903 --> 01:04:41,100
Two thousand yards to target, sir.

613
01:04:41,640 --> 01:04:42,834
Yankee cutter, downriver.

614
01:04:45,377 --> 01:04:47,641
You are now all in the custody
of the military...

615
01:04:47,813 --> 01:04:49,974
...of the United States of America.

616
01:04:50,149 --> 01:04:51,980
You will all be charged with treason.

617
01:04:52,317 --> 01:04:54,046
Quentin Turnbull...

618
01:04:54,219 --> 01:04:55,982
...you can show your face first.

619
01:04:58,290 --> 01:04:59,382
Arm the weapon.

620
01:05:20,746 --> 01:05:22,611
Fire at will.

621
01:05:25,717 --> 01:05:27,378
Lieutenant.

622
01:05:32,824 --> 01:05:34,086
Detonate.

623
01:05:49,208 --> 01:05:50,766
Full steam ahead.

624
01:05:56,848 --> 01:05:58,816
Can you shoot?

625
01:05:59,251 --> 01:06:00,548
Can you?

626
01:06:18,036 --> 01:06:19,970
Get to that gunner. I got you covered.

627
01:07:24,603 --> 01:07:26,230
Target is in range!

628
01:07:35,914 --> 01:07:37,176
Fire 50 rounds!

629
01:08:31,036 --> 01:08:32,401
Detonate the ordnance!

630
01:08:39,111 --> 01:08:40,874
<i>You're gonna go free.</i>

631
01:08:41,213 --> 01:08:44,182
<i>Free to walk this earth
with a mark on your flesh.</i>

632
01:08:44,349 --> 01:08:47,750
<i>And every day,
that mark will remind you...</i>

633
01:08:47,919 --> 01:08:51,446
<i>...of the man
who took everything you had.</i>

634
01:08:55,961 --> 01:08:57,326
Help! Jonah!

635
01:09:10,909 --> 01:09:13,639
No! No!

636
01:10:02,894 --> 01:10:03,986
I want you to watch.

637
01:10:04,563 --> 01:10:06,690
Watch this.

638
01:10:52,310 --> 01:10:53,834
Happy Fourth of July.

639
01:11:15,600 --> 01:11:17,227
Your reward.

640
01:11:20,138 --> 01:11:21,469
And full pardon.

641
01:11:22,741 --> 01:11:25,972
And I'd also like you to consider this.

642
01:11:30,882 --> 01:11:32,474
America needs a sheriff.

643
01:11:37,622 --> 01:11:41,820
I don't think countries
have sheriffs, exactly.

644
01:11:42,928 --> 01:11:44,555
Sir.

645
01:11:49,267 --> 01:11:52,031
Though if you get yourself into a jam...

646
01:11:52,203 --> 01:11:54,103
...I imagine you can find me.

647
01:12:05,350 --> 01:12:06,681
He offer you a job?

648
01:12:07,752 --> 01:12:09,652
- Yep.
- You take it?

649
01:12:11,256 --> 01:12:14,020
No. I'm not big on having a boss.

650
01:12:28,406 --> 01:12:30,340
Sorry about it, Jeb.

651
01:12:58,136 --> 01:13:02,436
<i>They say a man with vengeance
in his heart is supposed to dig two graves:</i>

652
01:13:02,607 --> 01:13:06,441
<i>One for his enemy and one for himself.</i>

653
01:13:06,611 --> 01:13:09,910
<i>Well, I guess mine will just have to wait.</i>

